FBIS3-47735 "dreas011_l_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 Philippines MNLF: Iran's Islamic Jihad Not in Mindanao BK1401055894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 14 Jan 94 BK1401055894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] A prominent Muslim leader denied the existence of an Islamic jihad in the Philippines. MNLF [Moro National Liberation Front] Reformist Group Chief, Makapanton Abbas says they have not heard any local chapter of the Islamic jihad, a group formed by Iranian extremist during the civil war in Lebanon. The group which claimed responsibility for the bombings in Davao City had called itself Islamic Jihad. Abbas maintains that rightist military elements are behind the bomb attacks.
